%20avoid%20watching%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-do-youtubers-make%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eads%20on%20YouTube%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsers%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20and%20other%20social%20media%20sites%2C%20have%20complained%20of%20a%20new%20pop-up%20on%20YouTube%20warning%20against%20the%20use%20of%20ad%20blockers%20in%20the%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FAlzter_S%2Fstatus%2F1711245948813500647%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScreenshots%20of%20the%20pop-up%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20that%20it%20warns%20users%20that%20ad%20blockers%20violate%20YouTube's%20terms%20of%20service.%20The%20message%20tells%20the%20user%20that%20their%20video%20will%20be%20blocked%20until%20they%20either%20remove%20the%20ad%20blocker%20or%20set%20it%20to%20allow%20YouTube%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20ever%20disable%20your%20AdBlocker%20and%20allow%20YouTube%20to%20run%20ads%20for%20your%20account%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20person%20wrote%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20show%20Google%20that%20you%20are%20willing%20to%20forgo%20your%20AdBlocker%20for%20YouTube%2C%20they%20will%20make%20this%20new%20AdBlock%20ban%20a%20permanent%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20message%20also%20encourages%20the%20user%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20YouTube%20Premium%2C%20the%20site's%20ad-free%20version%20which%20costs%20%2413.99%20per%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20YouTube%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20has%20launched%20%26quot%3Ba%20global%20effort%20to%20urge%20viewers%20with%20ad%20blockers%20enabled%20to%20allow%20ads%20on%20YouTube%20or%20try%20YouTube%20Premium%20for%20an%20ad-free%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20first%20started%20testing%20the%20feature%20on%20the%20website%20in%20June%2C%20the%20company%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F6%2F29%2F23778879%2Fyoutube-videos-disabling-a