9s%20only%20response%20was%20one%20tweet%20from%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20Put%20out%20on%20October%207%2C%20it%20has%20over%2027%20million%20views%20and%20was%20lacking%20in%20nuance%20%E2%80%93%20describing%20the%20attacks%20by%20Hamas%20as%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20attacks%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20expressing%20solidarity%20with%20Israel.%20The%20Foreign%20Ministry%20and%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20(EAM)%20S.%20Jaishanker%20had%20simply%20retweeted%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20tweet%20and%20left%20it%20at%20that.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20six%20days%20into%20the%20conflict%2C%20we%20have%20finally%20heard%20from%20the%20EAM%20spokesperson.%20But%20yet%20again%2C%20there%20is%20no%20direct%20re-assertion%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20support%20for%20the%20legitimate%20rights%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%20The%20statement%20makes%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20loss%20of%20Palestinian%20lives%20in%20the%20ongoing%20conflict.%20Without%20naming%20Israel%2C%20it%20just%20talks%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9Cobligation%20to%20observe%20international%20humanitarian%20law%E2%80%9D.%20The%20only%20attempt%20at%20striking%20a%20balance%20comes%20from%20mentioning%20the%20need%20to%20resume%20talks%20to%20establish%20a%20%E2%80%9Cviable%20State%20of%20Palestine%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20even%20this%20statement%2C%20that%20offers%20little%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20seems%20to%20be%20consciously%20delayed.%20It%E2%80%99s%20the%20immediate%20solidarity%20shown%20with%20Israel%2C%20by%20way%20of%20the%20tweet%20and%20the%20phone%20call%20made%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20to%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20which%20again%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20stands%20firmly%20with%20Israel%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20has%20registered%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20essential%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fear%20is%20that%20this%20lack%20of%20nuance%20may%20have%20been%20intended%2C%20and%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20may%20have%20erred%20in%20doing%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frooting-for-israel-not-a-good-word-about-palestine-modi-is-upending-indian-foreign-policy%5C%22%3ERooting%20for%20Israel%2C%20Not%20a%20Good%20Word%20About%20Palestine%3A%20Modi%20Is%20Upending%20Indian%20Foreign%20Policy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECertainly%2C%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20violence%20needs%20condemnation.%20But%20equally%20well-documented%20is%20the%20violence%20of%20the%20Israeli%20state%20against%20Palestinians.%20So%20whenever%20such%20violence%20has%20broken%20out%2C%20the%20approach%20of%20the%20Indian%20government%2C%20even%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20has%20invariably%20been%20to%20also%20underline%20the%20other%20side%E2%80%99s%20track%20record%20of%20violence%2C%20and%20also%20add%20the%20context%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20being%20denied%20their%20legitimate%20political%20rights%20by%20Israel.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20tweet%20left%20that%20out%2C%20and%20the%20EAM%20statement%20has%20barely%20mentioned%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20recently%20as%20May%202021%2C%20while%20responding%20to%20a%20cycle%20of%20violence%20between%20Hamas%20and%20the%20Israeli%20Defence%20Forces%20that%20had%20left%20over%20200%20people%20dead%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Permanent%20Representative%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20Ambassador%20T.S.%20Tirumurti%2C%20made%20a%20clearly%20more%20nuanced%20statement.%20He%20condemned%20the%20%E2%80%9Cindiscriminate%E2%80%9D%20rocket%20attacks%20by%20Hamas%2C%20described%20Israeli%20strikes%20as%20%E2%80%9Cretaliatory%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20at%20the%20same%20time%20underlined%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cunwavering%E2%80%9D%20commitment%20to%20the%20two-State%20solution.%20In%202014%2C%20too%2C%20even%20as%20India%20moved%20towards%20better%20relations%20with%20Israel%2C%20the%20then%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%2C%20the%20late%20Sushma%20Swaraj%2C%20had%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20fully%20support%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20Israel%20are%20very%20close%20today%2C%20an%20almost%20total%20inversion%20of%20the%20days%20when%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20one%20of%20PLO%20(Palestine%20Liberation%20Organisation)%20chief%20Yasser%20Arafat%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20supporters.%20India%20is%20now%20one%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20arms%20customers%2C%20and%20also%20of%20advanced%20and%20sensitive%20defence%20(and%20surveillance!)%20systems.%20This%20also%20underlines%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20%E2%80%98friendship%E2%80%99%20that%20has%20the%20blessings%20of%20the%20US.%20But%20even%20as%20India%20walks%20into%20the%20embrace%20of%20the%20US-Israel%20defence%20complex%2C%20one%20is%20not%20sure%20it%20cannot%20afford%20to%20ignore%20the%20sentiments%20of%20its%20Arab%20friends%20about%20Palestine%2C%20in%20the%20manner%20that%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%20tend%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20must%20also%20be%20noted%20that%20in%20Indira%E2%80%99s%20days%2C%20Hamas%20did%20not%20exist.%20Arafat%E2%80%99s%20PLO%20and%20Fatah%20were%20linked%20to%20a%20lower%20degree%20of%20violence%2C%20and%20showed%20a%20frequent%20readiness%20to%20be%20at%20the%20negotiation%20table%2C%20and%20so%20were%20easier%20to%20support%20against%20a%20continually%20belligerent%20Israel.%20In%20fact%2C%20in%201994%2C%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%201993%20Oslo%20Accords%2C%20that%20saw%20Arafat%20and%20the%20PLO%20historically%20recognising%20Israel%2C%20and%20also%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20National%20Authority%20(PNA)%2C%20as%20the%20de%20facto%20%E2%80%98Palestinian%20government%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20Arafat%20and%20two%20former%20Israeli%20prime%20ministers%2C%20Shimon%20Peres%20and%20Yitzhak%20Rabin%2C%20won%20the%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20the%20situation%20has%20worsened.%20Hardliners%20have%20a%20far%20greater%20say%20on%20both%20sides%20%E2%80%93%20Hamas%2C%20which%20practically%20controls%20Gaza%2C%20on%20one%20side%2C%20and%20a%20steady%20shift%20towards%20strongly%20right-wing%20governments%20in%20Israel%2C%20on%20the%20other%20side.%20Hamas%20and%20the%20IDF%20have%20been%20unrelenting%20in%20their%20violence.%20But%20even%20in%20this%20deteriorating%20climate%2C%20and%20despite%20a%20definite%20shift%20towards%20Israel%20by%20successive%20Indian%20governments%2C%20India%20has%20tried%20to%20walk%20a%20diplomatic%20tightrope.%20In%20May%202017%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20played%20host%20to%20Palestinian%20President%20Mahmoud%20Abbas%20and%20visited%20Israel%20two%20months%20later%2C%20the%20first%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20to%20do%20so.%20He%20followed%20that%20up%20by%20inviting%20Abbas%20to%20India%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhindutva-israel-tweets-palestine-conflict%5C%22%3EUnpacking%20the%20Hindutva%20Embrace%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20since%20then%20to%20now%2C%20one%20senses%20India%E2%80%99s%20increasing%20readiness%20to%20shrug%20off%20that%20fine%20balance.%20Partly%20because%20Hamas%20is%20now%20facing%20criticism%20from%20some%20Arab%20nations%2C%20including%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20UAE%2C%20who%20are%20also%20India%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20trade%20partners%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Both%20countries%20are%20also%20central%20to%20the%20recently%20announced%20ambitious%20India-Middle%20East-Europe%20Economic%20Corridor%20(IMEC)%2C%20along%20with%20Israel%20and%20Jordan.%20The%20feeling%20seems%20to%20be%20that%20India%20can%20now%20dispense%20with%20the%20nuance%20of%20empathising%20with%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20and%20still%20maintain%20ties%20with%20the%20Saudis%20and%20the%20UAE%20and%20other%20Arab%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20may%20have%20ignored%20some%20serious%20imponderables.%20The%20biggest%20is%20the%20dangerous%20appetite%20that%20both%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20have%20for%20violence.%20Both%20Iran-backed%20Hamas%20and%20US-backed%20Israel%20have%20the%20funding%2C%20the%20logistics%2C%20the%20arms%20and%20the%20motivation%20to%20be%20at%20war%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20Extended%20conflict%20would%20derail%20the%20IMEC%20indefinitely.%20Continued%20violence%20would%20also%20strain%20Saudi-Israeli%20ties%20which%20are%20only%20in%20their%20infancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20even%20thinking%20just%20selfishly%2C%20India%20must%20realise%20that%20it%20has%20a%20stake%20in%20peace%20in%20the%20region%2C%20and%20push%20hard%20for%20it.%20There%20is%20also%20the%20small%20matter%20of%20oil%20prices%2C%20that%20tend%20to%20spiral%20each%20time%20violence%20spirals%20in%20the%20middle-east.%20Rising%20oil%20prices%20have%20an%20inflationary%20impact%20on%20domestic%20prices%2C%20which%20the%20BJP%20would%20not%20want%20just%20a%20few%20weeks%20from%20key%20state%20assembly%20elections%20and%20just%20months%20away%20from%20a%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20apart%2C%20the%20historical%20fact%20is%20that%20India%20does%20have%20a%20special%20relationship%20with%20the%20Palestinians.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20non-Arab%20nation%20to%20recognise%20the%20PLO%2C%20and%20supported%20their%20cause%20for%20decades.%20And%20as%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20even%20the%20present%20government%20has%20a%20rapport%20with%20the%20Palestinian%20leadership%2C%20even%20if%20not%20with%20Hamas.%20It%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20in%20the%20unique%20position%20of%20having%20a%20robust%20relationship%20with%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20current%20conflict%2C%20something%20that%20almost%20none%20of%20the%20major%20players%20can%20claim.%20So%2C%20at%20a%20time%20like%20this%2C%20Instead%20of%20picking%20only%20Israel%2C%20it%20would%20serve%20India%20to%20be%20a%20vocal%20peacemaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20also%20look%20good%20on%20the%20Vishwaguru%E2%80%99s%20CV.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20fully%20explains%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20partisan%20tweet%20and%20the%20cagey%20EAM%20statement%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20would%20suggest%20that%20there%20is%20also%20a%20domestic%20aspect%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20choice%20of%20dropping%20the%20Palestinian%20cause.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20protesters%20against%20Indian%20authorities%20in%20the%20Kashmir%20Valley%20have%20repeatedly%20claimed%20to%20have%20been%20inspired%20by%20the%20protests%20in%20Palestine%20against%20Israeli%20forces%2C%20even%20equating%20protests%20in%20Srinagar%20with%20the%20Palestinian%20%E2%80%98intifada%E2%80%99%20of%201987%2C%20and%20their%20subsequent%20struggle%20over%20the%20years.%20This%20has%20been%20a%20sticking%20point%20with%20the%20mandarins%20in%20Delhi%2C%20particularly%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20there%E2%80%99s%20more.%20On%20October%209%2C%20four%20students%20of%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ffir-against-4-amu-students-for-marching-in-support-of-palestine-2719318%5C%22%3Ehad%20an%20FIR%20filed%20against%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20for%20raising%20slogans%20in%20support%20of%20Palestine%2C%20and%20against%20Israel.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20incident%20allowed%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20labour%20minister%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Raghuraj%20Singh%2C%20to%20describe%20AMU%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98hub%20of%20terrorists%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etvbharat.com%2Fenglish%2Fstate%2Futtar-pradesh%2Famu-has-become-nursery-of-terrorism-says-bjp-leader-on-university-students-supporting-palestine%2Fna20231009180024967967516%5C%22%3Echarge%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%E2%80%99s%20often%20been%20flung%20at%20the%20institution%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20it%20suits%20the%20BJP%20to%20conflate%20the%20rampant%20anti-Muslim%20climate%20that%20it%20is%20creating%20in%20India%20with%20the%20portrayal%20of%20the%20latest%20conflict%20in%20Gaza%20as%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20handiwork.%20This%2C%20while%20fully%20deleting%20the%20context%20of%20the%20violence%20that%20ordinary%20Palestinians%20have%20also%20faced%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20Israeli%20forces%20over%20the%20decades.%20Picking%20Israel%20over%20Palestine%20just%20for%20this%2C%20would%20undo%20years%20of%20empathetic%20and%20non-partisan%20statesmanship%20that%20India%20has%20demonstrated%20in%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20divided%2C%20most%20volatile%20conflict%20zones.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERohit%20Khanna%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20video%20storyteller.%20He%20has%20been%20managing%20editor%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Quint%2C%3Cem%3E%20and%20is%20a%20two-time%20Ramnath%20Goenka%20Award%20winner.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697368409000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F14143039%2F2018_1-14-Benjamin-Netanyahu-and-Narendra-Modi26231292_10159929705395165_4506447465273333604_n.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fby-siding-with-israel-india-is-jettisoning-decades-of-middle-east-statesmanship%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Clearly%2C%20it%20suits%20the%20BJP%20to%20conflate%20the%20rampant%20anti-Muslim%20climate%20that%20it%20is%20creating%20in%20India%20with%20the%20portrayal%20of%20the%20latest%20conflict%20in%20Gaza%20as%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20handiwork.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fby-siding-with-israel-india-is-jettisoning-decades-of-middle-east-statesmanship%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel-Hamas%20War%3A%20IDF%20Strikes%20Lebanese%20Territory%20After%20Military%20Post%20Attacked%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15135206%2FScreenshot-2023-10-15-at-1.51.16%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3