0cultural%20identity%20for%20Karnataka.%20It%20reads%20this%20ambivalently%20as%20summoning%20%E2%80%9Cunease%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20failure%E2%80%9D%2C%20conveying%20a%20lack%20of%20power%20for%20those%20who%20wish%20to%20mark%20their%20presence%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20repertoire%20of%20sub-regional%20languages%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20also%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20delicious%20freedom%E2%80%9D.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20book%20exploits%20this%20freedom%20to%20foreground%20what%20are%20mostly%20Kannada-language%20writers%2C%20film%20directors%2C%20actors%2C%20and%20even%20barbers%20as%20minor%20characters%20whose%20complexity%20has%20enabled%20a%20protagonist%20we%20glimpse%20in%20the%20background%3A%20an%20Indian%20federation%20owing%20its%20cultural%20pluralism%20to%20regional%20traditions%20of%20non-atheist%20socialism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20then%2C%20is%20the%20ethical%20stake%20that%20implicitly%20or%20explicitly%20threads%20the%20essays%20together%3A%20a%20commitment%20to%20taking%20religion%20seriously%20as%20a%20site%20of%20collective%20moral%20imagination%2C%20of%20inter-generationally%20produced%20images%20of%20virtue%20that%2C%20on%20the%20interpretation%20of%20the%20intellectuals%2C%20saints%20and%20artists%20Gowda%20focuses%20on%2C%20may%20orient%20and%20nuance%20distributive%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%20to%20the%20Marxist%20Sanskritist%20D.D.%20Kosambi%20(1907-66)%2C%20who%20tried%20to%20shoehorn%20the%20Carvakas%2C%20ancient%20Indian%20materialist%20philosophers%2C%20into%20his%20conception%20of%20them%20as%20proto-Marxist%20materialists%2C%20the%20villagers%2C%20artists%2C%20and%20authors%20in%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20essays%20effortlessly%20come%20across%20as%20indigenous%20socialists%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20they%20claim%20this%20label.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20selective%20conspectus%20of%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20themes%20should%20bring%20out%20its%20thematic%20variety%20and%20argumentative%20richness%3A%20we%20read%20of%20the%20recent%20waning%20of%20%E2%80%9Canimals%20as%20moral%20actors%E2%80%9D%20in%20Hindi%2C%20Tamil%2C%20and%20Kannada%20cinema%2C%20%E2%80%9Can%20impoverishment%20of%20worldview%3B%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Kannada%20film%20star%20Rajkumar%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20custodian%20of%20Kannada%20morality%E2%80%9D%20who%20%E2%80%9Cmoves%20smoothly%20across%20both%20modernity%20and%20tradition%E2%80%9D%20in%20his%20films%20set%20in%20the%20present%3B%20of%20how%20the%20great%20Kannada%20poet%20Kuvempu%E2%80%99s%20humanist%20critique%20of%20community%20identities%20as%20limiting%20led%20him%20to%20propose%20a%20new%20model%20of%20lost-cost%20marriage%20that%20crossed%20caste%20and%20religious%20lines%2C%20avoiding%20dowry%2C%20bride-price%20and%20horoscopes%3B%20of%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20women%20Sufi%20saints%20and%20their%20dargahs%20that%20are%20open%20to%20all%3B%20of%20the%2019th%20century%20Kannadiga%20Sufi%20Shishunala%20Sharif%E2%80%99s%20trans-communitarian%20piety%3B%20the%20debate%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20Kannada%20press%20over%20Kuvempu%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20exclusion%20of%20Madhvacharya%2C%20the%2013th%20century%20dualist%20Vedantin%20philosopher%20from%20Karnataka%2C%20from%20his%20hymn%20to%20Karnataka%20because%20Madhvacharya%20deemed%20Shudras%20and%20women%20unworthy%20or%20incapable%20of%20spiritual%20liberation%3B%20of%20the%20folklorist%20and%20Dalit%20leader%20Siddalingaiah%E2%80%99s%20initial%20disapproval%20of%20and%20eventual%20affection%20for%20the%20eccentric%20intimacy%20between%20villagers%20and%20their%20village%20deities%3B%20of%20Jayaprakash%20Narayan%E2%80%99s%20innovative%20socialist%20ideal%20of%20a%20non-violent%20and%20multi-part%20%E2%80%9Ctotal%20revolution%3B%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20trans-communitarian%20lyricism%20of%20the%20Kannada%20poet%20Nissar%20Ahmed%3B%20of%20the%20farmer%20Narayana%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20successful%20adoption%20of%20the%20Japanese%20natural%20farmer%20Fukuoka%E2%80%99s%20methods%20from%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EOne%20Straw%20Revolution%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20resume%20my%20opening%20metaphor%2C%20Karnataka%20thus%20comes%20across%20as%20a%20large%20realist%20novel%20made%20up%20wholly%20of%20morally%20particular%20minor%20characters%2C%20ranging%20in%20their%20moods%20from%20scholarly%20sobriety%20to%20folkloric%20hilarity%20and%20lyricism%3B%20and%20commanding%20genres%20that%20include%20political%20theory%2C%20poetry%2C%20folklore%2C%20theatre%2C%20journalism%2C%20cinema%2C%20and%20farming%20philosophy.%20That%20this%20cast%20of%20minor%20characters%20includes%20North%20Indian%20socialists%20like%20J.P.%20Narayan%20and%20Ram%20Manohar%20Lohia%20signals%20the%20openness%20to%20socialism%20that%20has%20distinguished%20the%20history%20of%20the%20old%20Mysore%20State%20from%20the%20Marxism%20that%20was%20prominent%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20the%20Ambedkarism%20prominent%20in%20Maharashtra.%20But%20Gail%20Omvedt%20who%20made%20this%20observation%20in%201994%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FDalits-Democratic-Revolution-Ambedkar-Movement%2Fdp%2F0803991401%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CLohiaism%2C%20then%2C%20did%20not%20come%20to%20Karnataka%20as%20an%20ideology%20of%20full-scale%20Dalit%20liberation%20but%20rather%20as%20a%20reformist%20trend%20which%20was%20in%20some%20ways%20compatible%20with%20the%20liberal%20co-optation%20patterns%20that%20had%20been%20established%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ERam-raj%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20atmosphere%20of%20the%20state.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOmvedt%20might%20have%20critiqued%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20book%20by%20arguing%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20stereotyped%20Karnataka%20identity%20and%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20openness%20to%20plural%20moral-religious%20visions%20are%20mutually%20complementary%20aspects%20of%20the%20same%20assimilationist%20and%20reformist%20rather%20than%20radical%20political%20culture.%20But%20let%20me%20conclude%20by%20proposing%20another%20frame%20of%20reference.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPhilosophical%20discussion%20of%20ethics%20has%20distinguished%20between%20deontology%2C%20consequentialism%2C%20and%20virtue%20ethics.%20Whereas%20deontological%20ethics%20prescribes%20rules%20for%20moral%20behaviour%20and%20consequentialism%20assesses%20actions%20by%20their%20moral%20consequences%2C%20virtue%20ethics%20concerns%20itself%20with%20moral%20states%20of%20being%20as%20ends%20in%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGowda%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20a%20contribution%20to%20virtue%20ethics%20and%2C%20as%20such%2C%20an%20implicit%20response%20to%20Alasdair%20MacIntyre%E2%80%99s%20(1981)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FAfter-Virtue-Study-Moral-Theory%2Fdp%2F0268035040%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAfter%20Virtue%3A%20A%20Study%20in%20Moral%20Theory%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20MacIntyre%20argues%20that%20the%20abandonment%20of%20Aristotelian%20ethics%20during%20the%20European%20Enlightenment%20was%20the%20abandonment%20of%20teleological%20ethics%2C%20of%20a%20collective%20consensus%20on%20where%20and%20how%20we%20want%20to%20end%20up%20by%20the%20practice%20of%20virtue.%20He%20opposed%20the%20individualist%20or%20subjective%20ethics%20that%20arose%20in%20its%20place%20by%20calling%20for%20a%20return%20to%20Aristotle%E2%80%99s%20model%20of%20community%20ethics%20oriented%20towards%20collective%20happiness.%20The%20many%20overlapping%20moral%20visions%20in%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20essays%20present%20small-scale%20and%20internally%20heterogeneous%20socialism%20as%20a%20collective%20ethical%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20essays%E2%80%99%20explorations%20of%20virtue%20ethics%20are%20distinguished%20by%20their%20recognition%20that%20virtue%20is%20more%20effectively%20taught%20and%20learned%20by%20stories%20about%20human%20individuals%20than%20by%20prescription%20(deontological%20ethics)%20or%20means-end%20reasoning%20(consequentialist%20ethics).%20Hence%2C%20the%20salience%20of%20personalities%20in%20these%20essays%3A%20Raj%20Kumar%2C%20Puneeth%20Rajkumar%2C%20Kuvempu%2C%20Siddalingiah%2C%20Elah%20Bhatt%2C%20Sara%20Aboobacker%2C%20and%20others.%20Each%20embodies%20her%20or%20his%20virtues%20because%20of%20their%20narrative%20frames%3A%20the%20films%20they%20act%20in%2C%20the%20novels%20or%20stories%20or%20plays%20they%20write%20and%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20own%20anecdotes%20about%20them.%20Virtue%20ethics%20that%20depend%20on%20narrative%20for%20its%20illocutionary%20force%20also%20depends%20on%20people%20who%20recognise%20its%20language%20(here%20Kannada%2C%20English%2C%20Hindi)%20and%20poetic%20conventions%20(here%20vacanas%2C%20a%20Sanskrit%20encyclopedia%2C%20folklore%2C%20theatre%2C%20Puranas%2C%20cinema%E2%80%A6)%20%E2%80%93%20in%20other%20words%2C%20an%20interpretive%20community.%20Karnataka%20is%20here%20an%20open%20set%20of%20interpretive%20communities%2C%20each%20purveyed%20to%20us%20by%20its%20morally%20eccentric%20minor%20character.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20value%20of%20this%20emphasis%20on%20narrative%20modes%20for%20virtue%20ethics%20is%20that%20it%20avoids%20oppressive%2C%20top-down%2C%20state-led%20projects%20that%20characterise%20deontological%20ethics%20(Plato%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ERepublic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EManusm%E1%B9%9Biti%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EShar%E2%80%98ia%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20leaving%20emulation%20up%20to%20the%20reader%20or%20listener%20and%20keeping%20space%20open%20for%20small-scale%20experimentation%2C%20relativism%20and%20humane%20openness%20to%20error.%20Whence%20the%20importance%20of%20humour%20to%20the%20Dalit%20intellectuals%20Siddalingiah%20and%20to%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20essays%20on%20them%2C%20humour%20that%20expresses%2C%20not%20the%20failure%20of%20reformist%20projects%2C%20but%20the%20impossibility%20of%20such%20an%20all-encompassing%20ethical%20project%20in%20the%20first%20place%3B%20and%20the%20necessity%20for%20ethical%20pluralism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20as%20elsewhere%2C%20the%20political%20ascendancy%20of%20fascist%20nationalism%20has%20been%20catastrophic%20for%20everyday%20ethics.%20This%20book%20offers%20reprieve%20to%20those%20of%20us%20not%20hypnotised%20by%20spectacles%20of%20nationalism%2C%20letting%20us%20turn%20from%20its%20glare%20towards%20the%20gentler%20lights%20of%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20many%20small-scale%20forays%20into%20socialist%20virtue%20ethics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrashant%20Keshavmurthy%20is%20associate%20professor%20of%20Persian-Iranian%20Studies%20at%20the%20Institute%20of%20Islamic%20Studies%2C%20McGill%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftn1%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fexploring-karnatakas-forays-into-socialist-virtue-ethics-and-minor-characters%23_ftnref1%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697364312000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15150558%2Fimage-1390.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fexploring-karnatakas-forays-into-socialist-virtue-ethics-and-minor-characters%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chandan%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20'Another%20India%3A%20Events%2C%20Memories%2C%20People'%C2%A0is%20an%20exploration%20of%20the%20open%20set%20of%20minor%20characters%20that%20make%20up%20cultural%20identities%20in%20modern%20Karnataka%2C%20displacing%20the%20protagonist%20that%20is%20India.%20This%20book%20comprises%20essays%20that%20complement%20this%20open-endedness.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fexploring-karnatakas-forays-into-socialist-virtue-ethics-and-minor-characters%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Muslims%20of%20North%20India%20Were%20Reduced%20to%20Being%20the%20Orphans%20of%20Partition%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15141523%2FAbul_Kalam_Azad_Ahmed_Saeed_and_Jawaharlal_Nehru_at_palam_Airport_on_July_19_1951.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EAnother%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20book%20by%20Pratinav%20Anil%20which%20deals%20with%20the%20making%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20Muslim%20minority%2C%20is%20a%20welcome%20addition%20to%20the%20literature%20of%20post-partition%20India%20looked%20at%20through%20the%20prism%20of%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20consequential%20minority.%20Anil%20is%20a%20lecturer%20in%20history%20at%20St.%20Edmund%20Hall%2C%20Oxford%20University%20who%20professes%20Marxist%20leanings.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%20examines%20how%20the%20Muslim%20community%20was%2C%20in%20the%20words%20of%20the%20author%2C%20%E2%80%9Cabandoned%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20Muslim%20leaders%20in%20the%20Congress.%20The%20time%20span%20for%20this%20study%20is%20from%201947-1977%2C%20going%20from%20the%20cataclysm%20of%20partition%2C%20the%20high%20noon%20of%20Nehruvian%20India%20to%20the%20excesses%20of%20the%20emergency%20and%20Sanjay%20Gandhi.%20It%20deals%20with%20the%20role%20of%20persons%20who%20were%20commonly%20termed%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esarkari%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Muslims%2C%20those%20that%20the%20Congress%20chose%20to%20give%20importance%20to%2C%20and%20what%20their%20agenda%20was%20%E2%80%93%20leaders%20such%20as%20Maulana%20Azad%2C%20Humayan%20Kabir%2C%20Rafi%20Ahmed%20Kidwai%2C%20Zakir%20Husain%2C%20Fakruddin%20Ahmed%20and%20others.%20It%20is%20a%20book%20rich%20in%20humour%20and%20anecdotes%20which%20centres%20around%20the%20usual%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%2C%20Jamia%2C%20and%20the%20distinguished%20landed%20families%20of%20North%20India%2C%20invariably%20tracing%20their%20relationship%20to%20the%20Nehrus%20and%20how%20they%20benefitted%20from%20this.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20340px)%2085vw%2C%20340px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15140842%2F71s669gqAWL._SL1500_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22340%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15140842%2F71s669gqAWL._SL1500_.jpg%20766w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15140842%2F71s669gqAWL._SL1500_-192x300.jpg%20192w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15140842%2F71s669gqAWL._SL1500_-654x1024.jpg%20654w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680208%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22532%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPratinav%20Anil%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EAnother%20India%3A%20The%20Making%20of%20the%20World%E2%80%99s%20Largest%20Muslim%20Minority%2C%201947%E2%80%9377%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EC%20Hurst%20%26amp%3B%20Co%20Publishers%20Ltd%20(March%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Muslim%20leadership%20in%20the%20Congress%20in%20many%20respects%20poses%20a%20very%20easy%20target%20%E2%80%93%20many%20of%20the%20leaders%20came%20from%20aristocratic%20backgrounds%2C%20Oxbridge%2C%20Aligarh%20and%20in%20most%20cases%20were%20misfits%20in%20the%20new%20India.%20They%20had%20lost%20their%20land%2C%20their%20language%20was%20consigned%20to%20the%20dustbin%20of%20history%2C%20and%20in%20a%20fundamental%20sense%2C%20their%20loyalty%20was%20always%20in%20question.%20They%20were%20largely%20powerless%20and%20their%20key%20role%20was%20to%20secure%20largesse%20or%20at%20any%20rate%20protect%20traditional%20institutions%20like%20Waqfs%2C%20educational%20institutions%2C%20etc.%20from%20state%20encroachment%20through%20party%20connections%20and%20pull.%20We%20will%20come%20to%20this%20agenda%20later%20on%2C%20as%20I%20think%20that%20Anil%20is%20a%20bit%20unfair%20to%20these%20hapless%20politicians.%20Let%20us%20remember%20that%20all%20elites%20are%20in%20some%20shape%20or%20form%20self-serving%20and%20the%20Muslims%20were%20not%20unique%20in%20this.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnil%20excels%20in%20debunking%20the%20mythology%20that%20the%20Muslims%20never%20had%20it%20so%20good%20as%20under%20Nehru%20%E2%80%93%20matters%20such%20as%20riots%20in%20Nehruvian%20India%20were%20all%20too%20pervasive.%20As%20he%20puts%20it%2C%20accounting%20for%20just%20under%20a%20tenth%20of%20the%20national%20population%2C%20they%20made%20up%2082%25%20of%20the%20fatalities%20and%2059%25%20of%20the%20injured.%20Another%20example%20of%20state%20brutality%20towards%20Muslims%20was%20the%20forced%20expulsion%2C%20particularly%20from%20Assam%20to%20East%20Pakistan%20at%20gunpoint%3B%20some%2035%2C000%20Muslims%20%E2%80%9Cconfessed%E2%80%9D%20to%20being%20Pakistanis%20and%20were%20deported.%20These%20are%20some%20of%20the%20most%20salient%20issues%20which%20come%20up%20and%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20Congress%20Muslims%20to%20deal%20with%20these%20depredations%20on%20their%20community.%20But%20this%20must%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20then%20Congress%20party.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnlike%20Nehru%2C%20the%20Hindu%20right%2C%20which%20populated%20the%20Congress%20leadership%20in%20the%20North%2C%20did%20not%20see%20the%20continuing%20presence%20of%20Muslims%20in%20India%20as%20an%20affirmation%20of%20a%20secular%20India.%20Sardar%20Patel%2C%20for%20all%20his%20public%20and%20private%20utterances%2C%20was%20content%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20least%20Muslims%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20encouraged%20the%20migration%20of%20Hindus%20from%20Pakistan%20and%20was%20keen%20on%20expelling%20Muslims%20to%20Pakistan%20irrespective%20of%20their%20desires.%20This%20is%20well%20documented.%20He%20was%20even%20initially%20against%20India%20claiming%20Kashmir%20as%20he%20saw%20this%20would%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20Muslims%20that%20India%20would%20have%20to%20deal%20with.%20It%20is%20this%20dichotomy%20of%20perceptions%20towards%20the%20minority%20which%20has%20bedevilled%20the%20Congress%20from%20partition%20until%20the%20Hindu%20right%20which%20emerged%20in%20the%201980s%20in%20a%20new%20and%20no-nonsense%20avatar.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20some%20extent%2C%20the%20reason%20for%20this%20effete%20leadership%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20in%20an%20apparent%20time%20warp%20%E2%80%93%20was%20the%20fact%2C%20which%20Anil%20dilates%20on%20in%20his%20book%20and%20which%20he%20correctly%20attributes%20to%20the%20sterling%20work%20of%20Paul%20Brass%20who%20points%20out%20that%20prior%20to%20partition%2C%20the%20Muslims%20of%20UP%20were%20relatively%20dynamic%2C%20there%20was%20a%20higher%20degree%20of%20urbanisation%20amongst%20young%20Muslims%20than%20Hindus%20and%20this%20led%20to%20disappointment%20as%20many%20educational%20positions%20had%20been%20taken%20by%20Hindus%20in%20colleges.%20This%20led%20to%20the%20formation%20of%20Urdu-speaking%20institutions%20where%20these%20Muslim%20migrants%20from%20the%20hinterland%20could%20join.%20Anil%20refers%20to%20the%20case%20of%20100%2C000%20Urdu-speaking%20Muslim%20students%20emigrating%20from%20the%20countryside%20to%20cities%20where%20there%20existed%20only%2020%2C000%20places%20in%20Hindi%20medium%20institutions.%20This%20meant%20that%20the%20balance%20of%2080%2C000%20students%20would%20create%20Urdu%20ones.%20These%20students%20from%20Urdu-speaking%20institutions%20were%20ready%20fodder%20and%20a%20vote%20bank%20for%20the%20Muslim%20League.%20This%20was%20demonstrated%20in%20the%201937%20election%2C%20when%20the%20League%20was%20able%20to%20secure%20half%20the%20votes%20from%20this%20constituency%20and%20nearly%2071%25%20in%20the%201946%20election.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20as%20Anil%20correctly%20surmises%2C%20this%20community%20had%20metamorphosed%20into%20a%20nation%20by%201947.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20separatist%20feeling%2C%20to%20a%20large%20extent%2C%20had%20been%20accentuated%20by%20policies%20of%20the%20Congress%20Government%20post-1937%20in%20the%20United%20Provinces%2C%20particularly%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Wardha%20Scheme%20of%20education%20into%20around%2016%2C000%20schools.%20Whilst%20identified%20with%20the%20Mahatma%2C%20in%20practice%2C%20according%20to%20Anil%2C%20this%20system%20of%20education%20%E2%80%9Cturned%20primary%20schools%20into%20centres%20of%20Hindu%20traditional%20learning%E2%80%9D.%20%C2%A0%20The%20fact%20that%20the%20Congress%20government%20under%20its%20education%20minister%20Dr%20Sampurnanand%20felt%20confident%20to%20introduce%20this%20educational%20system%20without%20any%20discussion%20in%20a%20state%20where%2025%25%20of%20the%20population%20were%20Muslims%20was%20for%20many%20in%20the%20community%20a%20harbinger%20of%20things%20to%20come.%20It%20also%20put%20the%20nationalist%20Muslims%20on%20the%20back%20foot%20as%20it%20was%20very%20difficult%20to%20distinguish%20Congress%20rule%20from%20the%20dreaded%20Hindu%20Raj%20that%20the%20League%20ranted%20about.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20people%20ask%20where%20was%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20and%20the%20Mahasabha%20at%20that%20time%2C%20most%20of%20the%20work%20of%20the%20Hindu%20right%20was%20undertaken%20by%20such%20Congress%20worthies%20as%20Pant%2C%20Sampurnanand%2C%20Tandon%20and%20others%20%E2%80%93%20who%20in%20the%20words%20of%20Joya%20Chatterji%20operated%20autonomously%20from%20Nehru.%20If%20one%20were%20to%20accuse%20the%20Muslim%20grandees%20who%20comprised%20the%20Congress%20leadership%20of%20a%20self-serving%20agenda%2C%20I%20do%20not%20think%20there%20was%20much%20more%20they%20could%20get%20done%20and%20neither%20could%20their%20great%20patron%2C%20Pandit%20Nehru%20who%20was%20personally%20horrified%20at%20the%20conduct%20of%20his%20partymen%20in%20UP.%20In%20relation%20to%20the%20anti-Urdu%20policy%2C%20he%20was%20constrained%20to%20comment%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20my%20colleagues%20do%20not%20agree%20I%20cannot%20help%20it.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F18143119%2FSIRSA-GENERAL-PICS.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F18143119%2FSIRSA-GENERAL-PICS.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F18143119%2FSIRSA-GENERAL-PICS-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F18143119%2FSIRSA-GENERAL-PICS-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-406264%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECongress%20flags.%20Photo%3A%20Bazil%20Ashrafi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fact%20was%20that%20the%20middle-class%2C%20upwardly%20mobile%20Muslim%20elite%20had%20largely%20migrated%20to%20Pakistan%20and%20left%20a%20huge%20vacuum%20which%20was%20filled%20by%20the%20Congress%20Muslims%20who%20were%20drawn%20from%20the%20landed%20class%20or%20were%20academics%3B%20and%20this%20perhaps%20is%20the%20most%20plausible%20explanation%20for%20this%20ineffectual%20leadership%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20curse%20of%20the%20majoritarianism%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20Muslims%20were%20spatially%20distributed%20in%20a%20way%20that%20made%20any%20Muslim%20party%20inconsequential%20in%20electoral%20terms.%20So%2C%20many%20Muslim%20Congressmen%20were%20beholden%20to%20the%20Congress%20for%20their%20seats%20and%20positions.%20You%20rarely%20bite%20the%20hand%20that%20feeds%20you.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhere%20Anil%20has%20a%20point%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20many%20of%20these%20Muslim%20politicians%2C%20upset%20with%20the%20Congress%2C%20did%20not%20consider%20forging%20alliances%20with%20other%20communities%20such%20as%20the%20Dalits%20in%20the%20way%20that%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20appears%20to%20be%20doing%20and%20partially%20succeeding.%20Perhaps%20that%20kind%20of%20thinking%20was%20something%20these%20conservative%20Muslims%20could%20not%20conceive%20of%20at%20the%20time%3B%20it%20was%20only%20a%20decade%20or%20so%20before%20they%20were%20entrenched%20in%20the%20ruling%20UP%20elite%2C%20revelling%20in%20a%20common%20culture%20with%20their%20Hindu%20raja%20friends%20and%20Pandits%20like%20Saprus%20and%20the%20Nehrus%2C%20who%20were%20part%20of%20this%20Urdu-Persian%20speaking%20hegemony.%20Many%20of%20the%20Muslim%20leaders%20who%20succeeded%20in%20this%20class%20were%20deeply%20religious%20and%20that%20also%20debarred%20them%20from%20reaching%20out%20to%20other%20communities%20as%20they%20were%20beset%20by%20religious%20parochialism.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reality%20which%20Anil%20appears%20to%20downplay%20is%20the%20very%20real%20dynamic%20of%20partition%20and%20its%20geographical%20and%20cultural%20consequences%2C%20on%20the%20two%20largest%20culturally%20self-sufficient%20provinces%2C%20the%20Punjab%20and%20Bengal%20were%20divided%2C%20causing%20the%20elevation%20of%20the%20cow%20belt%20and%20UP%20in%20particular%20and%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20notion%20of%20national%20identity.%20With%20the%20simulacrum%20of%20a%20Hindu%2C%20Hindi-speaking%20majority%2C%20as%20being%20the%20putative%20identity%20of%20the%20Indian%20State%2C%20the%20Muslims%20of%20North%20India%20were%20reduced%20to%20being%20the%20orphans%20of%20partition.%20This%20was%20not%20the%20case%20before%2C%20as%20some%20of%20the%20most%20radical%20and%20important%20reforms%20were%20implemented%20by%20Muslim%20politicians%20such%20as%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20%E2%80%93%20who%20introduced%20probably%20the%20most%20radical%20budget%20India%20has%20ever%20seen.%20Fazl%20ul%20Haq%20of%20Bengal%20introduced%20land%20reforms%20and%20an%20inclusive%20educational%20agenda%20in%20the%201940s%20and%201950s%20which%20explains%20the%20recent%20performance%20of%20Bangladesh%20as%20a%20rapidly%20growing%20export%20hub.%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20introduced%20radical%20land%20reforms%20in%20Kashmir%20and%20dismantled%20the%20vestiges%20of%20Dogra%20rule.%20So%20it%20would%20be%20wrong%20to%20identify%20Muslim%20politicians%20as%20only%20protecting%20Muslim%20religious%20interests%20and%20a%20self-serving%20agenda%20as%20they%20have%20been%20caricatured%2C%20and%20that%20unfortunately%20remains%20the%20takeaway%20of%20Anil%E2%80%99s%20book.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EJaved%20Gaya%20is%20a%20Bombay%20high%20court%20lawyer%20who%20is%20currently%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20the%20historical%2C%20geographical%20and%20political%20impact%20of%20partition%20on%20India%20and%20the%20wider%20sub-continent%2C%20particularly%20with%20reference%20to%20the%20Indian%20Muslims%20and%20other%20minorities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697362160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F15141523%2FAbul_Kalam_Azad_Ahmed_Saeed_and_Jawaharlal_Nehru_at_palam_Airport_on_July_19_1951.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fanother-india-book-review-muslims-orphans-of-partition%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Hindu%20right%20embedded%20in%20the%20Congress%20operated%20independent%20of%20Nehru%20and%20encouraged%20the%20migration%20of%20Muslims%20to%20Pakistan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fanother-india-book-review-muslims-orphans-of-partition%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20tiny%20gulf%20state%20of%20Qatar%20may%20end%20up%20playing%20an%20outsized%20role%20in%20Israel's%20hostage%20negotiations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697360880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-blinken-sheikh_6320459.jpg%3F20231013145019%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%