dy-appeals-to-lift-festival-ban-on-muslim-sellers-at-temple-fairs%2Fcid%2F1973429%5C%22%3Ethe%3Cem%3E%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20complained%20that%20Muslim%20vendors%20have%20been%20banned%20even%20from%20the%20government-run%20Mangaladevi%20Temple%20in%20Mangalore%2C%20Dakshina%20Kannada.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20several%20shrines%20had%20banned%20Muslims%20from%20bidding%20for%20stalls%20even%20in%20public%20spaces%20near%20the%20temples%20ahead%20of%20religious%20festivals%20in%20summer%20last%20year%20and%20later%20during%20Dasara.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Mangaladevi%20Temple%E2%80%99s%20management%20recently%20decided%20not%20to%20allot%20stalls%20to%20Muslim%20traders%20even%20on%20the%20street%20opposite%20the%20shrine.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20never%20faced%20such%20a%20ban%20until%20last%20year%20when%20some%20Hindu%20organisations%20objected%20to%20Muslim%20vendors%20setting%20up%20temporary%20stalls%20at%20temple%20fairs%2C%E2%80%9D%20committee%20convener%20B.K.%20Imthiyaz%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20we%20are%20now%20seeking%20permission%20(from%20district%20authorities%20in%20Dakshina%20Kannada%20and%20Udupi)%20to%20conduct%20our%20business%2C%20which%20is%20our%20livelihood.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EImthiyaz%20underscored%20that%20Muslims%20were%20not%20seeking%20permission%20to%20run%20stalls%20inside%20temple%20premises.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20we%20are%20asking%20is%20for%20permission%20to%20open%20stalls%20on%20public%20roads%20that%20come%20under%20the%20city%20civic%20body%20and%20not%20the%20temples%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20the%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ban%20on%20Muslim%20vendors%20participating%20in%20temple%20fairs%20in%20Karnataka%20started%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20hijab%20controversy%20in%20the%20state%2C%20which%20was%20under%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%